text: Roque de Garachico. Roque de Garachico is a small island or roque located off the north coast of the island of Tenerife (Canary Islands, Spain) belonging to the municipality of Garachico. It stretches north-south, and is up to wide, with an area of three hectares. It emerges steep out of the sea, with nearly vertical walls of rock in places, and reaches a height exceeding .
